A member of the South African National Defense Force (SANDF) approaches a group of people as he patrols in the streets of Hanover Park on July 18, 2019. JOHANNESBURG - The South African National Defence Force has started carrying out searches in Manenberg. That's after they were deployed on Thursday evening following a surge of shootings, gang violence and murders in Cape Town's crime-riddled townships. READ: SANDF deployed in Cape Town townships The soldiers are there to support the police and are expected to remain on the ground for no more than three months. Members of the South African National Defense Force(SANDF) patrol a street in Hanover Park on July 18, 2019. Members of South African National Defense Force (SANDF) patrol in the streets of Manenberg among inhabitants, on 18 July 2019, in Cape Town. Residents look on at members of the South African National Defense Force(SANDF) patrol a street in Hanover Park in Cape Town. Members of the South African National Defense Force(SANDF) patrol a street in Manenberg in Cape Town. The SANDF has been deployed in Manenberg in Cape Town on Thursday. Members of the South African National Defense Force (SANDF) climb upstairs to help police officers (unseen) for searches in a flat in Hanover Park on July 18, 2019. A convoy of South African National Defense Force (SANDF) drives through a street close to Manenberg in Cape Town. Residents gather in front of a member of the South African National Defense Force (SANDF) as he stands guard in front of a gate, during a patrol in the streets of Hanover Park on July 18, 2019. A woman carries a child through a broken gate as members of the South African National Defense Force (SANDF) patrol in the streets of Hanover Park, among inhabitants, on July 18, 2019.